item.title: PAPER FORMAT AND SUBMISSION
item.dc:creator: malilopezsjc
item.content:encoded:
Paper Selection Process

All submitted papers shall undergo a peer review process by the Saint Jude College - College of Information Technology Education (SJC - CITE)  Research Committee prior to acceptance. Authors of accepted papers (or unaccepted papers) shall be duly notified via email.

General Paper Guidelines

  • Use IEEE citation style
  • Single Spaced, Garamond Font, Size= 12
  • 15- 30 pages
  • Should be written in English

Application Process

  1. Send the abstract as paper entry to sjc-cite.sjc@phinmaed.com email address.
  2. The abstract should not exceed 700 words in .docx (MS Word) file format.
  3. Please indicate SUBJECT of the email as CITE_school or CITE 2023_name * if belonging to open participants, practicioners or professionals )
  4. The filename of the abstract should be "school_firstname". The "school" refers to the school of the participants is representing as to reflect in the Certificate of Recognition and the name of the participants if multiple authors.
  5. Successful entries will be emailed back with a LETTER OF ACCEPTANCE together with the bank details to which participant/ s will deposit payment. The corresponding fee is based on category (1) or (2) of the presenter/s.(please see program period/details/price).

    5.1 Please indicate in the email are the name, position and address of the person the LETTER OF ACCEPTANCE will be addressed. It is advised that any concerns pertaining to the application be stated also in the email.
    5.2 The total amount of fee of the entry will be based on the number of proponents stated in the abstract. However, if the other proponents will not be able to participate during the presentation, remaining member/ 2 may present in behalf. The fee is non-refundable in all aspects.

item.title: DRESS CODE
item.dc:creator: malilopezsjc
item.content:encoded:
A dress code is followed during the conference to maintain a professional culture.

Participants are highly advised to join the online conference in a business formal or semi-business formal attire. Sleeveless shirts, skirts above the knees, shorts, and open-toed footwear are STRICTLY not allowed.

item.title: Index
item.dc:creator: malilopezsjc
item.content:encoded:
Conference in Information Technology

Revolutionizing in Information Technology thru Research

The College of Information Technology Education is calling for papers related to Information Technology Research/Capstone Projects/Computer Science Thesis. The conference also accepts papers related to Education and Business in the Information Technology context. This is an invitation to Professionals, Academicians, Practitioners, and Students who are interested to submit original research papers for FACE-to-FACE or ONLINE oral presentation.

This endeavor is in correspondence with CHED Memorandum Order 25 series of 2015, Section 8 which states that the thesis and capstone project must be presented in a public forum. Forums may be international, national regional, or school-based conference, meeting, or seminar that is announced and open to interested parties.

The theme of the conference emphasizes the use of Revolutionizing Information Technology Thru Research.

SUITABLE RESEARCH/CAPSTONE TOPICS INCLUDE BUT ARE NOT LIMITED TO

1. Information Technology COVID19 Related Research

2. Custom Systems Implementation

3. Computer Education Based Research

4. Information Technology Entrepreneurship

5. Business Analytics and Data Science

6. Business Information Systems

7. Mobile Applications and Internet of Things (IoT)

8. Robot Interactions and Interfaces

9. Educational Technology and Technology Integrations

10. Cyber Security, Privacy and IT Ethics, Network Management

11. Information Systems in Education, Healthcare, Manufacturing and Transportation

12. Social Media and Digital Collaborations

13. Green Computing

14. Information Technology for Hospitality Management

15. Software as a Service (SaaS)
